result.execSummary:
The defendant Zackary R. Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Zackary R. Johnson does not appear in court. Nancy Bergstrom appears for Lincoln County. Cases are called. County is heard. Address of 504 E. 4th St. Merrill, WI, is deemed good. There is no return of mail service. Court makes finding of contempt; orders lump sum payment of $650.00 to be paid by Dec. 19, 2018; entry into payment plan in the amount of $100 per month beginnign on Jan. 15, 2019 and every month thereafter by the 15th until balance is paid in full. Thirty day jail sanction is STAYED w/Huber for failure to comply with lump sum payment and/or payment plan. Jail as sanction does not satisfy debt. Purge if taken into custody is $2000 or balance due if less than $2000.

  Pursuant to the provisions of Section 343.301, of the Wisconsin Statutes, the Court orders that for a period of 30 months,  each motor vehicle for which the defendant's name appears on the vehicle's certificate of title or registration be equipped with an ignition interlock device.

Also, pursuant to the provisions of Section 343.301, of the Wisconsin Statutes, the Court further orders that for a period of 30 months, beginning on the date the Department of Transportation issues any license to the defendant granted under Ch. 343, of the Wisconsin Statutes, the defendant's operating privileges for the operation of Class D vehicles be restricted to operating vehicles that are equipped with an ignition interlock device.
